actually participate,

00:52:26.470 --> 00:52:27.640
the government kind of went

00:52:27.640 --> 00:52:28.884
[EXPLOSION SOUND]

00:52:29.659 --> 00:52:31.700
And suddenly things just
kind of stopped working.

00:52:31.700 --> 00:52:34.050
And I think that
I'm concerned that,

00:52:34.050 --> 00:52:36.640
especially in my generation
and the generations coming up,

00:52:36.640 --> 00:52:38.931
there's a lack of trust that
the government is actually

00:52:38.931 --> 00:52:42.390
going to be able to do
anything to help us especially

00:52:42.390 --> 00:52:44.510
when it comes to stuff
like student loans,

00:52:44.510 --> 00:52:48.180
paying for college,
military spending,

00:52:48.180 --> 00:52:51.700
education for our future
children, social security.

00:52:51.700 --> 00:52:53.507
Do you have any
recommendations for how

00:52:53.507 --> 00:52:54.590
the government can go up--

00:52:54.590 --> 00:52:54.997
BARNEY FRANK: Yes!

00:52:54.997 --> 00:52:56.015
Just what I said.

00:52:56.015 --> 00:52:59.010
Cut military spending and stop
locking up people for drugs.

00:52:59.010 --> 00:53:01.930
And to you arguing
about the people

00:53:01.930 --> 00:53:03.722
are mad at the government.

00:53:03.722 --> 00:53:04.930
You know what the problem is?

00:53:04.930 --> 00:53:07.450
The people picked
the government.

00:53:07.450 --> 00:53:10.140
Why has the Tea Party
been so dominant?

00:53:10.140 --> 00:53:12.620
Because they win Republican
primaries and then people

00:53:12.620 --> 00:53:14.300
vote for them.

00:53:14.300 --> 00:53:16.926
Congress is not in
some bubble down there.

00:53:16.926 --> 00:53:18.800
Nobody serves in the
House of Representatives

00:53:18.800 --> 00:53:20.383
who didn't get more
votes than anybody

00:53:20.383 --> 00:53:22.240
else in the last
election for that job.

00:53:22.240 --> 00:53:24.050
And I understand
the vicious cycle.

00:53:24.050 --> 00:53:24.800
People get angry.

00:53:24.800 --> 00:53:26.660
Well, here's the
problem we have though.

00:53:26.660 --> 00:53:28.951
People on the right, when
they get angry at government,

00:53:28.951 --> 00:53:29.740
they vote.

00:53:29.740 --> 00:53:32.447
People on the left get angry
with government and they march.

00:53:32.447 --> 00:53:33.030
You know what?

00:53:33.030 --> 00:53:35.740
Voting beats marching if you're
trying to influence government.

00:53:35.740 --> 00:53:37.950
I mean Occupy and the Tea Party.

00:53:37.950 --> 00:53:40.110
Now, I didn't agree with
a lot of what Occupy did.

00:53:40.110 --> 00:53:43.390
I certainly was more in sympathy
with them than the Tea Party,

00:53:43.390 --> 00:53:45.860
but Occupy was a lot
of wasted effort.

00:53:45.860 --> 00:53:48.880
The Tea Party was a disciplined
get our people registered

00:53:48.880 --> 00:53:50.220
and vote.

00:53:50.220 --> 00:53:53.410
Now, I understand that people
get angry and they don't vote

00:53:53.410 --> 00:53:55.860
and it becomes worse.

00:53:55.860 --> 00:53:58.410
But the answer is clear with
the things you said-- improve

00:53:58.410 --> 00:54:00.530
college education,
accessibility,

00:54:00.530 --> 00:54:06.340
et cetera-- cut military
spending at the federal level.

00:54:06.340 --> 00:54:11.760
In every state the most serious
problem in the last 10 years

00:54:11.760 --> 00:54:15.689
has been the increase
in prison budgets.

00:54:15.689 --> 00:54:17.230
Look, you hit somebody
over the head,

00:54:17.230 --> 00:54:19.530
I would like there to be
a wall between you and me.

00:54:19.530 --> 00:54:21.590
I don't want violent
people hanging out.

00:54:21.590 --> 00:54:25.180
But people who are using drugs,
no reason to lock them up.

00:54:25.180 --> 00:54:27.790
And so those are the answers.

00:54:27.790 --> 00:54:29.910
Now, I understand
people are frustrated,

00:54:29.910 --> 00:54:31.740
but they need to go vote for
candidates that will do that.

00:54:31.740 --> 00:54:32.740
How much time do we got?

00:54:32.740 --> 00:54:34.260
I don't want to go over.

00:54:34.260 --> 00:54:35.570
What's our time here?

00:54:37.909 --> 00:54:39.450
Because I'm going
to sign some books,

00:54:39.450 --> 00:54:40.533
we got a few more minutes.

00:54:40.533 --> 00:54:41.620
Go ahead.

00:54:41.620 --> 00:54:44.660
AUDIENCE: The other thing that
happened around 2010, 2012

00:54:44.660 --> 00:54:49.380
is the Republican redistricting
that you alluded to earlier.

00:54:49.380 --> 00:54:53.930
We're coming up on 2020
and the census there

00:54:53.930 --> 00:54:55.800
and the redistricting there.

00:54:55.800 --> 00:54:59.970
Do you see a path forward
to not just continue

00:54:59.970 --> 00:55:02.620
fighting about who
gets to draw the lines

00:55:02.620 --> 00:55:05.740
to their own partisan advantage,
but to get to some system that

00:55:05.740 --> 00:55:08.069
is less volatile, less--

00:55:08.069 --> 00:55:10.110
BARNEY FRANK: Theoretically,
I thought there was.

00:55:10.110 --> 00:55:13.160
And there's a very disturbing
case now being argued

00:55:13.160 --> 00:55:15.030
before the Supreme Court.

00:55:15.030 --> 00:55:18.950
People in Arizona got a
petition to create a commission

00:55:18.950 --> 00:55:21.640
to take redistricting out of
the hands of the legislature

00:55:21.640 --> 00:55:25.890
where it almost inevitably
that kind of partisan fight

00:55:25.890 --> 00:55:27.930
and give it to a
nonpartisan commission.

00:55:27.930 --> 00:55:31.590
They did that in California and
they avoided gerrymandering.

00:55:31.590 --> 00:55:35.300
Unfortunately, the Constitution
says in far more specific terms

00:55:35.300 --> 00:55:38.970
than I wish it did-- and
this is for Congress--

00:55:38.970 --> 00:55:42.550
that the method of choosing
the members of Congress

00:55:42.550 --> 00:55:46.680
shall be decided by the
legislature in each state.

00:55:46.680 --> 00:55:51.880
And the legislators in Arizona
have gone to court and said,

00:55:51.880 --> 00:55:53.864
these people can't
have this referendum.

00:55:53.864 --> 00:55:55.280
We're the only
ones who can do it.

00:55:55.280 --> 00:55:57.200
And it sounded like
at the oral argument

00:55:57.200 --> 00:55:58.510
the court was going to do that.

00:55:58.510 --> 00:55:59.610
So that's the problem.

00:55:59.610 --> 00:56:01.110
There is a way and
there was this movement

00:56:01.110 --> 00:56:02.984
to do more of these
redistricting commissions

00:56:02.984 --> 00:56:05.235
in foreign and
elsewhere and I don't

00:56:05.235 --> 00:56:07.360
know what we can do about
that if the Supreme Court

00:56:07.360 --> 00:56:09.375
decides that because
there is an alternative

00:56:09.375 --> 00:56:11.500
and we may not get to it.

00:56:11.500 --> 00:56:12.000
OK.

00:56:12.000 --> 00:56:14.624
